    highlights: ["Two nights in Chefchaouen — Akchour hike option", "Asilah & Rabat Atlantic coast", "Fes medina full-day guided tour", "Volubilis Roman ruins", "Middle Atlas Barbary apes & cedar forests", "Erg Chebbi camel trek & desert camp", "Todra Gorge & Dades Valley", "Rose Valley & Skoura palmery", "Ait Benhaddou UNESCO kasbah", "Marrakech imperial sights"],
    price: "From €1,590",
    category: "long",
    itinerary: [
      { day: 1, title: "Casablanca → Rabat", route: "Casablanca → Rabat", desc: "Depart Casablanca northbound to Rabat, Morocco's stately capital. Visit the Hassan Tower, the Mausoleum of Mohammed V, and the Kasbah of the Udayas. Overnight in Rabat." },
      { day: 2, title: "Rabat → Asilah → Chefchaouen", route: "Rabat → Asilah → Chefchaouen", desc: "Head north along the Atlantic coast to Asilah — a whitewashed medina town painted with striking murals, ringed by Portuguese sea walls. Continue inland through the Rif Mountains to Chefchaouen, arriving in time to walk the luminous blue alleyways as the evening light turns everything to silver. Overnight in Chefchaouen." },
      { day: 3, title: "Chefchaouen: Blue Medina & Akchour", route: "Chefchaouen / Akchour Waterfalls", desc: "A full day in and around Chefchaouen. Explore the medina in depth — its dye-splashed staircases, flower-potted balconies, and the serene central plaza. In the afternoon, choose between a hike to the nearby Akchour waterfalls through forested valleys, or a leisurely ascent to the Spanish Mosque on the hillside above town for panoramic views across the Rif Mountains. Overnight in Chefchaouen." },
      { day: 4, title: "Chefchaouen → Volubilis → Meknes → Fes", route: "Chefchaouen → Volubilis → Meknes → Fes", desc: "Drive south to Volubilis, Morocco's finest Roman ruins where mosaics of gods and animals are remarkably preserved. Visit the sacred town of Moulay Idriss Zerhoun before continuing to Meknes and its monumental Bab Mansour gate. Arrive in Fes for overnight." },
      { day: 5, title: "Fes: Medieval City Full Day", route: "Fes Medina", desc: "Explore Fes el-Bali with a licensed local guide: the Al-Qarawiyyin Mosque and university (the oldest in the world), the Bou Inania Madrasa, the Chouara tanneries where hides are cured in stone vats of natural pigment, and the bustling craft souks. Overnight in Fes." },
      { day: 6, title: "Fes → Middle Atlas → Merzouga → Sahara", route: "Fes → Ifrane → Azrou → Midelt → Ziz Valley → Merzouga", desc: "Cross the Middle Atlas — alpine meadows, cedar forests with Barbary macaques at Azrou, and the dramatic Ziz Gorge lined with six million palm trees. Arrive at Merzouga as the sun sinks. Camel trek into the Erg Chebbi dunes for a Berber camp dinner, traditional music, and star-filled skies. Overnight in the desert camp." },
      { day: 7, title: "Desert Sunrise → Rissani → Todra Gorge → Dades Valley", route: "Merzouga → Rissani → Todra Canyon → Dades Valley", desc: "Watch the sunrise paint the dunes in shades of orange and rose. Return by camel and visit the ancient souk of Rissani. Drive west through the awe-inspiring Todra Gorge — sheer 300-metre walls rising from a stream-fed canyon floor — and continue to the kasbahs and rock formations of the Dades Valley. Overnight in the Dades Valley." },
      { day: 8, title: "Dades → Rose Valley → Skoura → Ait Benhaddou → Marrakech", route: "Dades Valley → Rose Valley → Skoura → Ouarzazate → Ait Benhaddou → Tizi n'Tichka → Marrakech", desc: "Drive through the Valley of Roses and the Skoura oasis of ancient kasbahs. Pass through Ouarzazate and visit Ait Benhaddou, the UNESCO-listed fortified village perched above a dry riverbed. Cross the High Atlas on the Tichka Pass and descend to the warmth of Marrakech. Overnight in Marrakech." },
      { day: 9, title: "Marrakech Sightseeing", route: "Marrakech Medina", desc: "A guided day in the ochre city: Koutoubia Mosque, Saadian Tombs, Bahia Palace, Majorelle Garden, and the heady perfume of the spice souk. Sunset at Jemaa el-Fna, where snake charmers, acrobats, and traditional cooks create a spectacle unlike anywhere else on earth. Overnight in Marrakech." },
      { day: 10, title: "Marrakech → Casablanca", route: "Marrakech → Casablanca", desc: "A final morning at leisure in Marrakech for a hammam session or last souk visit, before the afternoon transfer to Casablanca. Overnight in Casablanca." },
      { day: 11, title: "Casablanca Departure", route: "Casablanca → Airport", desc: "Airport transfer to Mohammed V International Airport. End of tour services." },
    ],
    included: ["Transport in air-conditioned 4WD or minivan", "English-speaking driver/guide", "9 nights in hotels & riads (dinner & breakfast)", "1 night in Sahara desert camp (dinner & breakfast)", "Sunset & sunrise camel trek", "All entrance fees", "Travel insurance (vehicle)"],
